y, P., James, F., Alan, H., Carbon monoxide poisoning (2009) New Eng. J. Med, 360, pp. 1217-1225; McCulloch, M.T., Langford, N., Duxbury, G., Real- time trace- level detection of carbon dioxide and ethylene in car exhaust gases (2005) Appl. Opt, 44. , 2887-2884; Abeles, F.B., Heggestad, H.E., Ethylene: An urban air pollutant (1973) J. Air Pollut. Cont. Assoc, 23, pp. 517-521; Weidmann, D., Kosterev, A.A., Roller, C., Curtel, R.F., Fraser, M.P., Tittel, F.K., Monitoring of ethylene by a pulsed quantun cascade laser (2004) Appl. Opt, 43, pp. 151-155; Baird, C., (2002) Environmental Chemistry, , 2nd ed.; Brookman: Porto Alegre, Brazil; Seinfeld, J.H., Urban air pollution: State of the science (1989) Science, 243, pp. 745-752; Lefohn, S., Foley, J.K., Establishing relevant ozone standards to protect vegetation and human health: Exposure/dose-response considerations (1993) J. Air Waste Manage. Assoc, 43, pp. 106-112; Atkinson, R., Atmospheric chemistry of VOCs and NOx (2000) Atmosph. Environ, 34, pp. 2063-2101; Wolf, G.T., Korsog, P.E., Ozone control strategies based on the ratio of volatile organic compound to nitrogen oxides (1992) J. Air Waste Manage. Assoc, 42, pp. 1173-1177; Seinfeld, J.H., (1986) Atmospheric Chemistry and Physics of Air Pollution, , John Wiley & Sons: Hoboken, NJ, USA; Cristescu, S.M., Persijn, S.T., Hekkert, S., Harren, F.J.M., Laser-based systems for trace gas detection in life sciences (2008) Appl. Phys. B, 92, pp. 343-349; Berrou, A., Raybaut, M., Godard, A., Lefebvre, M., High-resolution photoacoustic and direct absorption spectroscopy of main greenhouse gases by use of a pulsed entangled cavity doubly resonant OPO (2010) Appl. Phys. B, 98, pp. 217-230; Thomas, S., Photoacoustic Spectroscopy for process analysis (2006) Anal. Bioanal. Chem, 384, pp. 1071-1086; Sigrist, M.W., Bartlome, R., Marinov, D., Rey, J.M., Vogler, D.E., Wächter, H., Trace gas monitoring with infrared laser-based detection schemes (2008) Appl. Phys. B, 90, pp. 289-300; Ang